32. Below is a non-exhaustive list of pairs of crypto-assets which should not be considered
as belonging to the same type of crypto-assets for the purpose of the reverse solicitation
exemption:
• utility tokens, asset-referenced tokens or electronic money tokens;
• crypto-assets not stored or transferred using the same technology;
• electronic money tokens not referencing the same official currency;

• asset-referenced tokens based mostly on FIAT currencies and asset-referenced
tokens having significant crypto-currency ponderations;
• liquid and illiquid crypto-assets;
• crypto-assets other than asset-reference tokens and electronic money tokens
with a non-identifiable-offeror and crypto-assets other than asset-reference
tokens and electronic money tokens with an identifiable offeror.
